title: Add builtin clawq_help tool with topic-based help and onboarding guidance
---
Add a new built-in tool `clawq_help` with an optional `topic` string parameter. This tool serves as an in-session help system for the agent and its users.

When called without a topic (or with topic='general'):
- List available help topics
- Provide general info about clawq (what it is, version, key capabilities)
- Mention clawq.org/llms-full.txt as the full self-knowledge reference
- Point to clawq.org/quickstart for first-time setup

When called with a topic:
- Return focused help for that topic area
- Topics should cover: tools, channels, config, skills, agents, memory, background-tasks, subagents, security, models, web-ui, crons, git-worktrees, onboarding

The tool should tie into existing doc content:
- clawq.org/llms-full.txt (already injected into prompt, line 744 of prompt_builder.ml)
- clawq.org docs pages (quickstart, configuration, cli-reference, channels, tools, skills, etc.)
- Config wizard flow for new users
- Feature onboarding guidance (e.g. Claude Tag parity features, room agents, structured pipelines)

Implementation notes:
- New file: src/tools_builtin_help.ml (following existing tools_builtin_*.ml pattern)
- Register in tools_builtin.ml alongside other builtins
- Tool data sources: static topic content + dynamic config/runtime info where useful
- Keep initial topic set concise; expand based on usage patterns
- 43 existing builtin tools across 12 modules — this is a meta/help tool, not a functional one

Related: B756 (UX/onboarding review)